This paper discusses the use and challenges of software obfuscation in Android applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves surveying developers and analyzing a large dataset of Android apps, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of integrated development environments (IDEs), which could relate to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
